\lim_{n \to \infty} a_n
x/2
n\in \mathbb{N}
\frac{x+2x+3x+\ldots +nx-n}{n^2}\leq a_n\leq \frac{x+2x+3x+\ldots +nx}{n^2},
 \begin{align*} \lim_{n\to \infty} \frac{x+2x+3x+\ldots +nx}{n^2} &= \lim_{n\to \infty} \sum _{k=1}^{n} \frac{1}{n}\cdot \frac{k}{n}x\\ &= \lim_{n\to \infty} \sum _{k=1}^{n} \frac{1-0}{n}\cdot \left( 0 + \frac{(1-0)k}{n} \right)x\\ &= \int_0 ^1 tx \text{ dt}\\ &= \frac{x}{2}. \end{align*} 
\frac{x}{2}\leq \lim_{n\to \infty} a_n\leq \frac{x}{2}.
